headline: Palo Alto Stock Tumbles After Earnings. Why Some Analysts Still Say Buy.
summary: Palo Alto Networks  stock was falling sharply on Wednesday amid investor disappointment over the cybersecurity company’s financial results—but some analysts think now is still the time to buy.  Palo Alto  on Tuesday evening reported third-quarter adjusted earnings of 80 cents a share on revenue of $2.29 billion.  The cybersecurity company also said it expects fourth-quarter earnings in the range of 87 cents a share to 89 cents a share, compared to analyst estimates of 87 cents a share.
